definitions.820-00165: What is 820-00165? a LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER.

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00165</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> <SIGNAL>SMS_INT_L</SIGNAL> (<RESISTOR>R5193</RESISTOR>)
threads.message: <RESISTOR>R5193</RESISTOR> is gone, very corroded and the pads are gone, is this an important resistor or function?

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00165</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> <SIGNAL>SMS_INT_L</SIGNAL> (<RESISTOR>R5193</RESISTOR>)
threads.message:
There is a note on page 37:
"If SMS interrupt is not used, pull up to SMC rail"
Does your board work without <RESISTOR>R5193</RESISTOR>?
If yes, you may live as is.
But test it few days, sleeping, suspend, restarts...

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00165</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> <SIGNAL>SMS_INT_L</SIGNAL> (<RESISTOR>R5193</RESISTOR>)
threads.message:
Board is heavily liquid damaged, im working on replacing all that has corrosion and is not working, however when diagnosing <RESISTOR>R5193</RESISTOR> came right off and the pads are gone, so no real way of knowing if thats the exact problem.

I will report back when all is fixed.
